##The late director of the Wuchang Hospital, "a man who worked his ass off. " 

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

By Tang Qi, Liao Yan, Wen Xiaoxiao, Xue Shasha, _ thepaper.cn _

Interns Zhao Yumeng and Xia Mengjie

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Funeral vehicle for Liu Zhiming's body arrives. Tang Qitu, the paper

Before the funeral home vehicle arrives, many people keep silent, some people take off the mask from time to time, wipe the tear.

On the morning of February 18, the Hubei Provincial Health Commission and the Wuhan Municipal Health Commission both announced that Liu Zhiming, deputy secretary of the Party Committee and Director of the Wuchang Hospital in Wuhan, died on the same day after he was unluckily infected in the fight against the new pneumonia epidemic, he was 51 years old.

Seven medical staff have died in the line of duty in the fight against the new outbreak of pneumonia.

Before his death, Liu Zhiming was most concerned with those who had come into contact with him.

A colleague who saw him off at the scene told The Paper that Liu had asked people to protect themselves first, and that he was worried about people who had come into contact with him. He'd feel guilty if something happened to someone else.

"send off your comrades. "

At about 12:00 on the 18th, the outpatient building and Inpatient Department of Tongji Zhongfa new court were very quiet and almost no one moved around.

However, just the night before, there was news that "Liu Zhiming, director of the Wuchang Hospital in Wuhan, had been treated at the Tongji china-france new hospital because his condition had worsened after being infected with new crown pneumonia" , that made the hospital, far from the city, the focus of attention.

On the morning of February 18, officials announced the death of Liu Zhiming.

Officials said Liu Zhiming, regardless of his personal safety, led the medical staff of Wuchang Hospital to fight against the epidemic and made an important contribution to the prevention and control of Wuhan's new pneumonia.

"I am a teacher and a friend, and I will see you in the next life, " a chief doctor at Wuchang Hospital wrote in a circle of friends after learning of the Dean's death. On the 18th, he accompanied his family and colleagues of Wuchang Hospital to wait for Liu Zhiming's departure outside the Tongji Chinese-french New Era University College Hospital.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Screenshots of memorials posted by colleagues

Before the funeral home vehicle arrives, many people keep silent, some people take off the mask from time to time, wipe the tear. At about 1500 hours, Liu Zhiming's body was taken to the funeral home's car. His family members supported each other. His wife, Cai, was wearing a isolation suit. The car moved slowly, and she cried as she followed it out of the hospital.

"He wanted us to take precautions first, he was worried about the people he came in contact with, and he asked us to keep asking each other, " a Wuchang Hospital worker who had been waiting told The Paper news, after Liu Zhiming contracted the disease, he always wanted to ask everyone he came into contact with, asking if they were okay. He said he felt bad if something happened to someone else.

"How (the person) left, did not have time to see him one last time. He is our comrade-in-arms, I can only use 'send comrade-in-arms' (to express) . " The staff member sobbed.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Family members hold each other as Liu Zhiming's body is released from the hospital.

To fight the plague with his wife

His wife, Ms Choi, is also a medical staff member in the front line of the fight against the disease. She is the head nurse of the Intensive Care Unit of the Guanggu district of Wuhan Third Hospital. She has been working almost seven hours a day in the intensive care unit since the outbreak of the new pneumonia.

On January 21, Cai received a phone call from Liu Zhiming, who told her that Wuchang Hospital, as a designated hospital for fever in Wuhan, would transfer patients within two days, transform the hospital area and receive fever patients, the Changjiang daily reported earlier. She was worried because Liu Zhiming had a "cold" and had a low-grade fever for a week. She was worried that his body would not be able to support him.

At the time, the two men did not know that the fever was a symptom of neocoronary pneumonia. But Ms. Chua was a little worried and reminded her husband, "but he was too busy working and didn't have time for this, and people weren't as alert as they are now. "

January 22 at 4:00, she again received a call from Liu Zhiming, asked her to help pack up a little change of clothes to send, because as a designated hospital he can not go home. But the next afternoon, when she got the call again, she was told that viral pneumonia had been admitted to the intensive care unit.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Liu Zhiming died in Tongji Hospital in the sino-french New City Hospital district rescue

Liu has been in increasingly poor health since then, the report said. SATS are down to 80. Ms. Cai wanted to take care of Liu Zhiming many times, but she refused.

On February 3, Liu Zhiming was put on a respirator because of his critical condition. Cai in the wechat video, again to take care of him. At the other end of the screen, Liu Zhiming, who could not speak, shook his head.

"A man who works hard. "

Tang Jie (not his real name) , the chief of neurosurgery at a third-tier hospital in Beijing, had met Liu Zhiming at many conferences when he was also the chief of neurosurgery at Wuhan's Third Hospital before being transferred to Wuchang Hospital.

"We've all seen him at meetings. He's from Shiyan, Hubei. He's more outgoing, he's more sociable. He is not only with me, including many of our colleagues are quite familiar with, people are more forthright. And he's not old, he's only two or three years older than us, so it's not a bad age,"Tang told thepaper.cn.

"He seems to have been infected for quite a long time, " Tang said of Liu's new pneumonia. "It was just not that bad a while ago. We heard that he was in good condition about three days ago. "

Liu Zhiming's former colleague Shi Yan (not her real name) said she learned of the news this morning when she saw that many former colleagues had sent a group of friends to mourn Liu. Liu came to Wuchang in 2015 to work as a vice president at the hospital, where he founded the Department of neurosurgery, Shi recalled. After the former president of the hospital retired, Liu Zhiming served as president.

"Many colleagues commented that Liu is 'a person who works hard' , " Shi said, adding that Liu is tall and elegant. He works hard and is gentle with others.

On the afternoon of the 18th, Liu Zhiming was seen off by not only his family members and colleagues, but also the heads of government departments at all levels. Yu Xuejun, vice-director of the National Health Commission, Yang Yunyan, vice-governor of Hubei Province, and Zhou Xianwang, mayor of Wuhan, visited the new court in Tongji to pay their respects to Liu Zhiming's family. They praised Liu Zhiming as a "model" , a "pioneer" and a "hero" .
